# Settings
trainImageDir = "Train/images"
trainMaskDir = "Train/masks"
valImageDir = "Validation/images"
valMaskDir = "Validation/masks"
batchSize = 32
overlapPercentage = 0.25
tileSize = (144*2, 108*2)

trainImagePaths = sorted(glob(os.path.join(trainImageDir, "*.jpg")))
trainMaskPaths = sorted(glob(os.path.join(trainMaskDir, "*.png")))

trainGenerator = customDataGenerator(imgPath=trainImagePaths,
                                     maskPath=trainMaskPaths,
                                     batchSize=batchSize,
                                     tileSize=tileSize, 
                                     shuffle=True,
                                     augment=True,
                                     overlap=True,
                                     overlapPercentage=overlapPercentage)

valImagePaths = sorted(glob(os.path.join(valImageDir, "*.jpg")))
valMaskPaths = sorted(glob(os.path.join(valMaskDir, "*.png")))

valGenerator = customDataGenerator(imgPath=valImagePaths,
                                     maskPath=valMaskPaths,
                                     batchSize=batchSize,
                                     tileSize=tileSize, 
                                     shuffle=True,
                                     augment=False,
                                     overlap=True,
                                     overlapPercentage=overlapPercentage)

X, y = trainGenerator.take()

print(f"Image batch shape: {X.shape}")
print(f"Mask batch shape: {y.shape}")

nToPlot = 1
for i in range(X.shape[0]): 

    img = X[i]
    mask = y[i]

    # Plot image and mask
    plt.figure(figsize=(5, 2))
    
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=1)
    plt.title("Image")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(mask, cmap='gray', vmin=0, vmax=1)  # Use squeeze to remove extra dimensions
    plt.title("Mask")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.show()

    if i == nToPlot-1:
        break

# Create U-Net model
model = unet_model(input_size=(tileSize[0], tileSize[1], 1))

# Compile with Adam optimizer and dice loss
model.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.Adam(learning_rate=1e-3),
              loss=tf.keras.losses.Dice(),
              metrics=[tf.keras.metrics.BinaryIoU(target_class_ids=[1], threshold=0.5)])

# Print model summary
model.summary()

if train:
    
    # Early stopping callback
    es =  tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor="val_binary_io_u",
                                           mode="max",
                                           patience=20,
                                           restore_best_weights=True)

    # Train U-Net model
    model.fit(trainGenerator,
              validation_data=valGenerator,
              epochs=200,
              verbose=0,
              callbacks=[es, TqdmCallback(verbose=1)])

In[16]:
if train:

    nEpochs = np.arange(1, len(model.history.history['loss'])+1)

    bestEpoch = nEpochs[np.argmax(model.history.history['val_binary_io_u'])]

    # Plot loss and validation loss
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(nEpochs, model.history.history["loss"], label="Train Loss")
    plt.plot(nEpochs, model.history.history["val_loss"], label="Validation Loss")
    plt.axvline(bestEpoch, linestyle="dashed", color="tab:red", label="Best Epoch")
    plt.xlabel("Epoch")
    plt.ylabel("Loss")
    plt.title("Dice Loss")
    plt.xticks(nEpochs[::5]) # Every 5 epochs
    plt.grid()
    plt.legend()

    # Plot validation IoU metric
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(nEpochs, model.history.history["binary_io_u"], label="Train IoU")
    plt.plot(nEpochs, model.history.history["val_binary_io_u"], label='Validation IoU')
    plt.axvline(bestEpoch, linestyle="dashed", color="tab:red", label="Best Epoch")
    plt.xlabel("Epoch")
    plt.ylabel("IoU Score")
    plt.title("Binary IoU")
    plt.xticks(nEpochs[::5]) # Every 5 epochs
    plt.grid()
    plt.legend()

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# Select if you want to use the keras or ONNX exported model
mode = ["onnx", "keras"]
mode = mode[0]

print(f"Selected {mode} model for predictions")

# Loading the model
if mode == "onnx":
    ort_session = ort.InferenceSession("model.onnx") # Load the ONNX model

elif mode == "keras":
    model.load_weights("model.keras") # Load Keras model

In[19]:
# Fetching one batch from the validation data to inspect the model result
X, y = valGenerator.take()

# Number of images to plot
nToPlot = 5

for i in range(X.shape[0]): 
     
    # Extract real X and y from validation data
    img = X[i]
    mask = y[i]
   
    if mode == "onnx":

        # Prepare input data
        input_data = np.expand_dims(img, axis=0).astype(np.float32)

        # Get the name of the input
        input_name = ort_session.get_inputs()[0].name

        # Run inference
        ort_outputs = ort_session.run(None, {input_name: input_data})

        # ort_outputs are a list of numpy arrays, one for each output of the model
        #print(f"ONNX Runtime output shape: {ort_outputs[0].shape}")

    elif mode == "keras":

        # Run inference
        mask_predicted = model.predict(np.expand_dims(img, axis=0))
    

    # Plot image and mask and predicted segmentation mask
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
    plt.imshow(img, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Image")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
    plt.imshow(255*mask, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Mask")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.subplot(1, 3, 3)
    if mode == "onnx":
        plt.imshow(np.squeeze(ort_outputs[0]), cmap="gray")
    elif mode == "keras":
        plt.imshow(255*mask_predicted.squeeze(), cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Predicted Mask")
    plt.axis('off')

    plt.show()

    if i==nToPlot-1:
        break

In[26]:
# Show or save the figure
displayMode = ["show", "save"]
displayMode = displayMode[0]

# Number of images to plot
nToPlot = 20

# Load all image paths
image_paths = load_images(inputDir)[:nToPlot]

# Process images
if mode == "onnx":
    ort_session = ort.InferenceSession("model.onnx")
    results = process_images(image_paths, tileParams, ort_session=ort_session, modeSelected=mode)
elif mode == "keras":
    model = tf.keras.models.load_model("model.keras")
    results = process_images(image_paths, tileParams, model=model, modeSelected=mode)


# Saving results
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

for result in tqdm(results, desc="Showing/Saving segmentation images"):

    binarizedSegmentation = result['segmentation']>0.5

    img_name = os.path.basename(result['image_path'])
    output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, f"seg_{img_name}")
    
    # Optionally visualize
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
    plt.imshow(np.array(Image.open(result['image_path'])))
    plt.title("Original Image")
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
    plt.imshow(binarizedSegmentation, cmap='gray')
    plt.title("Predicted segmentation mask")

    plt.subplot(1, 3, 3)
    plt.imshow(np.array(Image.open(result['image_path'])))
    plotBwImage((255*binarizedSegmentation).astype("int"))
    plt.title("Overlaid segmentation mask")
    
    if displayMode == "save":
        plt.savefig(os.path.join(output_dir, f"vis_{img_name}"), dpi=900, bbox_inches="tight")
        plt.close()

    elif displayMode == "show":
        plt.show()

print(f"Processed {len(results)} images. Results saved to {output_dir}")
